Document Summary – MantaRay Enclosure Preparation

This document outlines the step-by-step process required to prepare the MantaRay Enclosure for assembly. It details each stage of the build, including enclosure preparation, plate installation, labeling, harness integration, battery mounting, and installation of the panel mount frame. The goal is to ensure consistency, accuracy, and efficiency across all stages of production.

Work Completed

I developed a structured build document that organizes the enclosure preparation process into clearly defined sections. Each subsection identifies the task, responsible work area (such as Cortek or the Machine Shop), and a brief description of the procedure involved. This ensures that each team understands their role and the sequence of operations.

Information Gathering

The information was gathered by reviewing current workflows, consulting with relevant departments (including Cortek and the Machine Shop), and observing the actual build and assembly process. This helped ensure that the document reflects real-world practices and aligns with how work is currently performed.

Challenges Faced

One of the main challenges was consolidating information from multiple sources and teams into a single, coherent document. There were also inconsistencies in how tasks were previously described or executed, which required clarification and standardization. Additionally, ensuring the correct sequence of steps and avoiding missing dependencies between tasks required careful attention.

Outcome

The result is a clear, organized build document that standardizes the enclosure preparation process. It improves communication between teams, reduces ambiguity, and serves as a reliable reference for both current and future builds.

Problem Solved

This document addresses the lack of a unified and structured process for preparing the MantaRay Enclosure. By clearly defining each step and responsibility, it reduces errors, improves efficiency, and ensures a more consistent build quality across all units.
